{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.7",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 7 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:1",
      "text": "My son, keep my words, and hide with thee my commandments. 1a My son, honour the Lord, and thou shalt be strong; and fear none but him:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:2",
      "text": "keep my commandments, and thou shalt live; and keep my words as the pupils of thine eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:3",
      "text": "And bind them on thy fingers, and write them on the table of thine heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:4",
      "text": "Say that wisdom is thy sister, and gain prudence as an acquaintance for thyself;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:5",
      "text": "that she may keep thee from the strange and wicked woman, if she should assail thee with flattering words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:6",
      "text": "For she looks from a window out of her house into the streets, at one whom she may see of the senseless ones, a young man void of understanding,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:7",
      "text": "passing by the corner in the passages near her house,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:8",
      "text": "and speaking, in the dark of the evening,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:9",
      "text": "when there happens to be the stillness of night and of darkness:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:10",
      "text": "and the woman meets him having the appearance of a harlot, that causes the hearts of young men to flutter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:11",
      "text": "And she is fickle, and debauched, and her feet abide not at home.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:12",
      "text": "For at one time she wanders without, and at another time she lies in wait in the streets, at every corner.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:13",
      "text": "Then she caught him, and kissed him, and with an impudent face said to him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:14",
      "text": "I have a peace-offering; to-day I pay my vows:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:15",
      "text": "therefore I came forth to meet thee, desiring thy face; and I have found thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:16",
      "text": "I have spread my bed with sheets, and I have covered it with double tapestry from Egypt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:17",
      "text": "I have sprinkled my couch with saffron, and my house with cinnamon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:18",
      "text": "Come, and let us enjoy love until the morning; come, and let us embrace in love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:19",
      "text": "For my husband is not at home, but is gone on a long journey,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:20",
      "text": "having taken in his hand a bundle of money: after many days he will return to his house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:21",
      "text": "So with much converse she prevailed on him to go astray, and with the snares of her lips she forced him from the right path.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:22",
      "text": "And he followed her, being gently led on, and that as an ox is led to the slaughter, and as a dog to bonds, or as a hart shot in the liver with an arrow:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:23",
      "text": "and he hastens as a bird into a snare, not knowing that he is running for his life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:24",
      "text": "Now then, my son, hearken to me, and attend to the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:25",
      "text": "Let not thine heart turn aside to her ways:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:26",
      "text": "for she has wounded and cast down many, and those whom she has slain are innumerable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.7.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:27",
      "text": "Her house is the way of hell, leading down to the chambers of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
